1184
01:46:16,078 --> 01:46:18,955
My name's John Edward Gammell.

1185
01:46:19,040 --> 01:46:20,081
Cheer up.

1186
01:46:20,166 --> 01:46:22,917
There's plenty of John G.'s for us to find.

1187
01:46:26,297 --> 01:46:28,715
All you do is moan.

1188
01:46:28,799 --> 01:46:31,134
I'm the one that has to live
with what you've done.

1189
01:46:31,218 --> 01:46:32,927
I'm the one that put it all together.

1190
01:46:33,012 --> 01:46:37,682
You wander around, you're playing detective.
You're living a dream, kid.

1191
01:46:37,767 --> 01:46:41,853
A dead wife to pine for.
A sense of purpose to your life.

1192
01:46:41,937 --> 01:46:45,273
A romantic quest that you wouldn't end
even if I wasn't in the picture.

1193
01:46:46,567 --> 01:46:49,736
- I should kill you.
- Quit it. Lenny, come on.

1194
01:46:49,820 --> 01:46:52,822
You're not a killer.
That's why you're so good at it.

1195
01:46:56,368 --> 01:46:59,120
What are you doing?
You know what time it is?

1196
01:46:59,205 --> 01:47:01,289
It's beer o'clock. I'm buying.

1197
01:47:03,292 --> 01:47:04,417
Fuck.

1198
01:47:14,512 --> 01:47:15,637
<i>I'm not a killer.

1199
01:47:16,931 --> 01:47:19,474
<i>I'm just someone who wanted
to make things right.

1200
01:47:25,523 --> 01:47:27,899
<i>Can I just let myself forget
what you've told me?

1201
01:47:45,126 --> 01:47:48,503
<i>Can I just let myself forget
what you made me do?

1202
01:48:02,768 --> 01:48:04,519
<i>You think I just want another puzzle to solve?

1203
01:48:05,354 --> 01:48:07,522
<i>Another John G. To look for?

1204
01:48:08,732 --> 01:48:10,608
<i>You're a John G.

1205
01:48:12,319 --> 01:48:14,404
<i>So you can be my John G.

1206
01:48:22,872 --> 01:48:24,998
<i>Do I lie to myself to be happy?

1207
01:48:26,292 --> 01:48:28,042
<i>In your case, Teddy...

1208
01:48:29,170 --> 01:48:31,087
<i>Yes, I will.

1209
01:48:44,226 --> 01:48:46,311
Hey, that's not your car!

1210
01:48:46,395 --> 01:48:48,980
- It is now.
- Jesus Christ, you can't take it!

1211
01:48:49,064 --> 01:48:51,983
- Why not?
- Because the guy you just killed owns it!

1212
01:48:52,067 --> 01:48:53,776
Somebody'll recognize it!

1213
01:48:55,237 --> 01:48:58,323
I think I'd rather be mistaken
for a dead guy than a killer.

1214
01:48:59,283 --> 01:49:01,784
I might hang on to this for a while.

1215
01:49:02,620 --> 01:49:03,912
Lenny.

1216
01:49:05,956 --> 01:49:08,458
Will you help me find the keys?

1217
01:49:08,542 --> 01:49:10,293
Help me find my keys.

1218
01:49:32,566 --> 01:49:35,860
<i>I have to believe in a world
outside my own mind.

1219
01:49:35,945 --> 01:49:38,112
<i>I have to believe that
my actions still have meaning...

1220
01:49:38,197 --> 01:49:40,156
<i>even if I can't remember them.

1221
01:49:42,326 --> 01:49:44,994
<i>I have to believe
that when my eyes are closed...

1222
01:49:45,079 --> 01:49:47,163
<i>the world's still here.

1223
01:49:48,374 --> 01:49:50,792
<i>Do I believe the world's still here?

1224
01:49:53,712 --> 01:49:55,296
<i>Is it still out there?

1225
01:49:59,134 --> 01:50:00,134
<i>Yeah.

1226
01:50:02,513 --> 01:50:05,306
<i>We all need mirrors
to remind ourselves who we are.

1227
01:50:07,643 --> 01:50:09,352
<i>I'm no different.

1228
01:50:22,658 --> 01:50:24,450
<i>Now, where was I?

1229
01:50:26,666 --> 01:50:30,000
Edited by Sonah